  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Social peace in Lebanon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Inter and intra refugee and host community relationships are facing increased tensions due to the multiple crises that have affected Lebanon since the end of 2019 in addition to longstanding structural problems. There are negative perceptions of each community towards the other &#x2013; blaming &#x201C;Them&#x201D; for the suffering of &#x201C;Us&#x201D;. This could lead to an increase in violence and increased pressure on the government to facilitate the return of Syrian refugees to an unsafe environment. These negative perceptions are reinforced by competition over jobs and services, the aid perception bias (reinforced by non-conflict sensitive interventions) and the lack of dialogue and social engagement spaces which deteriorated further due to the COVID-19 pandemic (whose impact was higher on women), and the emerging needs, amid the economic and political crises.
This project aims to contribute to social peace in Lebanon through the provision of self-care and conflict sensitivity interventions with NGOs and through the social peace programme with communities affected by conflict.</narrative>
  </description>
